		<a name="top" id="top"></a>
		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Lindbergh kidnapping</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:284px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Lindbergh_baby_poster.jpg" class="image" title="Lindbergh baby kidnapping poster."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/ce/Lindbergh_baby_poster.jpg" width="282" height="482" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">Lindbergh baby kidnapping poster.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>The <b>kidnapping of Charles Augustus Lindbergh, Jr.</b>, son of <a href="/wiki/Aviator" title="Aviator">aviator</a> <a href="/wiki/Charles_Lindbergh" title="Charles Lindbergh">Charles Lindbergh</a> and <a href="/wiki/Anne_Morrow_Lindbergh" title="Anne Morrow Lindbergh">Anne Morrow Lindbergh</a>, occurred in 1932 when the toddler was <a href="/wiki/Child_abduction" title="Child abduction">abducted</a> from his family home in <a href="/wiki/East_Amwell,_New_Jersey" title="East Amwell, New Jersey" class="mw-redirect">East Amwell, New Jersey</a> (near the town of <a href="/wiki/Hopewell,_New_Jersey" title="Hopewell, New Jersey">Hopewell</a>). The boy was subsequently murdered.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>Newspaper writer <a href="/wiki/H.L._Mencken" title="H.L. Mencken" class="mw-redirect">H.L. Mencken</a> called the kidnapping and subsequent trial "the biggest story since the <a href="/wiki/Resurrection_of_Jesus" title="Resurrection of Jesus">Resurrection</a>."<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup>.</p>
<p><a href="/wiki/Bruno_Hauptmann" title="Bruno Hauptmann">Bruno Hauptmann</a> was convicted of the crime and executed by electric chair, though he proclaimed his innocence.</p>
<p>The crime inspired the "<a href="/wiki/Federal_Kidnapping_Act" title="Federal Kidnapping Act">Lindbergh Law</a>," which made <a href="/wiki/Kidnapping" title="Kidnapping">kidnapping</a> a <a href="/wiki/Federal_crime" title="Federal crime">federal crime</a>.</p>
